Checking Audio Data

Kendra Wyant

2020-08-13

  • Notes

  • Descriptives

Notes

This script checks data from RISK participants’ transcribed audio check-ins by computing descriptives and checking for missingness and potential errors.

Setup

Paths

path_data <- "./analysis/shared/data"

Packages

library(tidyverse)
library(janitor)
library(lubridate)
library(kableExtra)
library(psych)
library(tidytext)
library(tm)
library(textclean)
library(textrecipes)

Import Data and glimpse

Audio data

audio <- read_rds(file.path(path_data, "ds_audio.rds"))  
audio <- audio %>%
  clean_names() %>% 
  rename("subid" = "sub_id") %>% 
  mutate(date_central = date(as_datetime(utc, tz = 'America/Chicago'))) %>%
  glimpse()

163 participants contribute to a total of 7593 audio recordings.
The earliest audio recording is from 2017-03-02 and the last is from 2017-03-02.
This is because there is only 1 unique utc for entire utc column.
As a result this script only will be checking message text characteristics and descriptives overall and by subid.

Missing (NA) values

if(any(is.na(audio))){
  missing <- audio %>%
    summarise(across(everything(), ~sum(is.na(.)))) %>%
    gather(key = "var", value = "num_NA" ) %>%
    filter(num_NA > 0)
  missing %>%
    kable(caption = "Variables with missing values", table.attr = "style='width:40%;'") %>%
    kable_styling(position = "left", bootstrap_options = "condensed")
}else {
  paste("No missing values")
}

contains_inaudible_total <- contains_inaudible %>% 
  group_by(subid) %>% 
  summarise(n_obs = n()) %>% 
  filter(n_obs > 20) 

contains_inaudible_total %>%   
  kable(caption = "Participants with more than 20 messages containing inaudible in entire dataset",
        table.attr = "style = 'width:50%;'") %>% 
  kable_styling(position = "left")
Participants with more than 20 messages containing inaudible in entire dataset
subid n_obs
242 26

356 audio recordings have “inaudible” in transcription. However only 30 are short enough (less than 100 characters) for it to likely be a problem. Of these shorter inaudible messages, subid 242 makes up 19 (63.3%) of them.
Of the entire dataset subid 242 has a total of 26 messages containing inaudible transcription in them.

Number of audio messages per participant

audio %>% 
  group_by(subid) %>% 
  summarise(n_obs = n()) %>% 
  summarise(mean = round(mean(n_obs), 2),
            sd = round(sd(n_obs), 2),

            max = max(n_obs)) %>% 
  kable(caption = "Average audio messages per participant",

text analyses

Clean text

audio_tidy <- audio %>% 
      mutate(text = removeNumbers(text)) %>%
      mutate(text = tolower(text))%>% 
      mutate(text = removePunctuation(text)) %>% 
      mutate(text = replace_symbol(text)) %>% 
      mutate(text = stripWhitespace(text)) # condenses whitespace into a single space

# Remove new blank text tokens for word count statistics
audio_tidy <- audio_tidy %>% 
  filter(!text == " " & !text == "")

Tokenize text data (tidy text)

audio_tidy <- audio_tidy %>% 
  unnest_tokens(word, text) %>% 
  glimpse()
## Rows: 503,238
## Columns: 2

Get ML features

audio_features <- audio_tidy %>%
  anti_join(get_stopwords(), by = "word") %>%
  count(subid, word) %>%
  bind_tf_idf(word, subid, n) %>%
